  (text "UNO Q HUB75 SHIELD — Rev 0.3 — BLOCK DIAGRAM\n\nSignal flow (IEEE 315: left to right, power top to bottom):\n\n  J4 (+5V_EXT) ──> [POWER] ──> +3V3 (AMS1117), +5V_EXT_HUB75 (direct)\n  J2 (UNO Q JSPI) ──> [UNO Q INTERFACE] ──> SPI3 slave to ESP32-S3\n  [ESP32-S3] ──> HUB75 GPIO ──> [HUB75 DRIVER] ──> J1 IDC ──> Panel\n  [ESP32-S3] ──> I2S ──> [AUDIO CODEC] ──> J_LINEOUT / J_MIC\n  [ESP32-S3] ──> SPI2 + I2C ──> [DISPLAY] ──> J6 FPC ──> 5\" TFT + GT911\n  [UNO Q MCU] ──> I2C ──> [CONNECTIVITY] ──> J8/J9 Qwiic, J10-J14 Grove\n\nESP32-S3-WROOM-1-N16R8: 16MB flash, 8MB PSRAM, CO-PROCESSOR ONLY\n  NO wireless role. WiFi/BLE handled by ESP32-C6 on Super Carrier.\n  GPIO35/36/37: NC (consumed by octal PSRAM internally)\n  GPIO0: 10k pullup to +3V3 (boot-safe; CS_S3_MPU on carrier)\n  OE on both 74HCT245: tied LOW in hardware (no GPIO needed)\n  UART0 superseded by USB CDC on GPIO19/20 (J5 USB-C)\n\nSub-sheets:\n  sheets/power.kicad_sch        AMS1117-3.3, AGND/DGND star, FB1 ferrite, indicators\n  sheets/uno_q_interface.kicad_sch  J2 SPI3, J3 UART debug header\n  sheets/esp32s3.kicad_sch      WROOM-1-N16R8, decoupling, EN/GPIO0 pullups, USB-C\n  sheets/hub75_driver.kicad_sch 74HCT245 x2, HUB75 2x8 IDC, OE/DIR tied LOW\n  sheets/audio_codec.kicad_sch  ES8388, AVDD ferrite, DC-block caps, line-out, mic-in\n  sheets/display.kicad_sch      22-pin FPC, SPI2 display, GT911 touch, BL PWM, JP1\n  sheets/connectivity.kicad_sch Qwiic x2, Grove x5 (all from STM32U585)"
    (at 20 260 0) (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27)) (justify left top)))
)
